The fifth annual HR Congress starts in Mombasa on Wednesday. It’s theme is “Humanise the workplace for productivity: Achieve Vision 2030.” The three day congress slated for Whitesands Hotel will discuss” the HR function of 2030: What can today’s HR professionals begin to do to people for the future.” It will also tackle the role of HR as the pillar and engine of economic growth, employment and wealth creation. The professionals will also discuss humanised work place with Oserian Development Company as a case study, 100 per cent human at work network with Safaricom Ltd as case study and emotional and social intelligence at the work place: The case of soft power to improve productivity. The congress will look into possibility of humanising the public sector, the new work place environment; finding balance between fixed, flexible and social media.